<!--
  New-GPTImage.md — Standard file (optional)

  If a file named New-GPTImage.md exists next to the script (the name is set by the
  "standardFile" key in the .conf), its content is automatically appended to EVERY
  prompt you send, after a blank line. Use it to define a default style, quality
  directives, or constraints that should apply to all your generations without
  retyping them each time.

  To use it: copy this file to "New-GPTImage.md" and replace the example below with
  your own text. If the file is empty or absent, nothing is appended and the prompt
  is sent as-is.

  This .example file is only a template: your real New-GPTImage.md is ignored by
  git (see .gitignore) so your personal style directives are never published.

  Remove this comment block in your real file — its content would be appended to
  the prompt as-is.
-->

Style: cinematic, high detail, natural lighting.
Avoid: text, watermarks, distorted anatomy.
